    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="730"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11683.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs having been informed by the Chilean Minister at
                    Washington that the President of the United States would accept the good offices
                    of Chile, Argentina and Brazil in the Mexican crisis, has instructed him to act
                    with his Brazilian and’ Argentine colleagues in this sense. He has called the
                    Mexican Chargé d’Affaires in Chile to make similar offer through him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
